description: From eye dialectal spelling of right.

adjectives.description: reet (comparative mair reet, superlative maist reet)

examples: 2011,  “Awterations”, in  Bread and Fishes‎[1], performed by Houghton Weavers:Now I've only bin once wi a scarf round mi neck, And I moan't go agin, no not me will I eck. Now it doesn't seem reet if mi memory jogs, Goin down for a pint in thi bowtie and clogs.
